$ SSMS Menu: Tools -> Options -> Environment -> Documents

Settings that can be changed under *Tools -> Options -> Environment -> Documents* include
  • Detect when file is changed outside the environment (and: Reload modified files unless there are unsvaed changes)
  • Allow editing of read-only files; wanr when attempt to save
  • Open file using directory of currently active dcoument
  • Check for consisten line endings on load
  • Display warning when global undo will modify edited files
  • Show Miscellaneous files in Solution Explorer (and number of items saved in the Miscellaneous files project)
  • Save documents as → development/Unicode when data cannot be saved in codepage

